<HL> Magna Group Acquisition</HL>
<DD> 03/13/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> MAGI
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN>
<DATELINE> BELLEVILLE, Ill.  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Magna Group Inc. said it agreed to acquire First Granite Bancorp., Granite City, Ill., in a stock swap valued at about $27 million. 

   Magna said it will exchange 2.175 of its common shares for each of First Granite's 675,000 shares. 
In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Magna closed at $18.25, unchanged. 

   Magna, a financial services company, has assets of about $1.5 billion. 
First Granite, a bank holding company, has assets of about $186.5 million. 

</TEXT>
